==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Endamage
<hw>En*dam"age</hw> <pr>(?; 48)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Endamaged</conjf> <pr>(?;
48)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Endamaging</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>en-</ets> + <ets>damage</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>endommager</ets>.]</ety> <def>To bring loss or damage to; to
harm; to injure.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The trial hath <qex>endamaged</qex> thee no way.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Endamageable</ent>⟦br⟧
